organic_results.title: A further note on the collegiate scholar: The question of value congruence
organic_results.snippet: The case made in an earlier paper for extending the Clark-Trow typology of college student subcultures to encompass that of the collegiate scholar rested entirely on data collected at a public university. The present paper extends the data base for analysis to show that those originally categorized as collegiate scholars closely resemble in value outlook their counterparts at Ivy League-type schools and, in turn, differ markedly in value outlook from lower-class youth found in the job corps.
